# 7. Web Frameworks Simplify Server-Side Web Programming

Building a server-side application from scratch can be repetitive and time-consuming. A **web framework** provides ready-made tools that simplify common backend tasks such as handling requests, managing URLs, processing responses, and organizing application code.

Instead of writing every feature manually, developers can focus on building the application's functionality while the framework handles much of the underlying infrastructure.

### Popular Web Frameworks

| Language | Framework |
|----------|-----------|
| Python | Django |
| Python | Flask |
| Python | FastAPI |
| JavaScript | Express.js |
| Java | Spring Boot |

> **Note:** We will study these frameworks in detail in later lectures.

---

# 8. Summary

- Modern web applications follow the **client–server architecture**.
- The **client** sends requests, while the **server** processes them and returns responses.
- **Web servers** receive client requests and deliver website resources.
- **HTTP** is the protocol used for communication between clients and servers.
- **Static websites** deliver the same content to every visitor.
- **Dynamic websites** generate content based on users, data, and application logic.
- Dynamic websites require **backend programming**.
- **Web frameworks** simplify backend development by providing reusable tools and structures.

